<constraints>
- Target 400-600 lines.
- All API endpoints must specify HTTP method, path, auth requirements, request schema, response schema, and error codes.
- Data model must include field names, types, constraints (nullable, unique, indexed), and foreign key relationships.
- Architecture section must reference the pattern detected in the brownfield scan and explain how this feature integrates.
- Security section must address authentication, authorization, input validation, and relevant OWASP concerns.
- Performance section must state measurable targets (p95 latency, throughput, memory budget).
- Dependencies must include version constraints where detectable from the brownfield scan.
- Do not repeat product requirements — reference product.md for personas and user stories.
- Do not describe QA processes — that belongs in quality.md.
</constraints>

